---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="FAQ" description="Common questions about booking The Greenway Band">

  <!-- Inner Page Hero -->
  <section class="faq-hero">
    <span class="faq-label" data-reveal>FAQ</span>
    <h1 class="faq-hero__title" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">Common questions</h1>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Accordion -->
  <section class="faq-accordion" data-reveal>
    <div class="faq-accordion__inner">

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How many musicians are in The Greenway Band?</span>
          <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-item__answer">
          <p>The Greenway Band performs as a 10 to 20 piece ensemble depending on your venue, your guest count, and the energy you're going for. Every configuration includes a full rhythm section, vocalists, and a horn line. Adrian walks through the options on your first call and recommends a setup based on your room and your crowd.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What does "10 piece" actually mean?</span>
          <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-item__answer">
          <p>A 10 piece lineup typically includes drums, bass, guitar, keys, two to three vocalists, and a horn section. As we scale up, we add more horns, more vocalists, and more depth to the arrangements. At 10 pieces, you've got a full band. At 20, you've got a show.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How much space does the band need on stage?</span>
          <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-item__answer">
          <p>A 10 piece needs roughly 16 by 12 feet minimum. A full 20 piece needs closer to 24 by 16 feet. We send a detailed stage plot to your venue and planner well before the event, and we'll work around the space you have.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How does pricing work?</span>
          <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-item__answer">
          <p>We price by configuration and performance length, and every event has different logistics. Adrian walks through the numbers on your first call. No PDF price list, but no guesswork either. You'll know exactly what you're paying for and why.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Do you travel outside of Houston?</span>
          <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-item__answer">
          <p>Yes. We're based in Houston and perform across Texas and beyond. Adrian covers travel logistics and any associated costs on your first call.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Can we request specific songs?</span>
          <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-item__answer">
          <p>Yes. After you book, you'll get a song request process where you can share must plays, do not plays, and general direction for the set. Our music director arranges everything for live performance, so if a song isn't already in our book, we'll learn it and rehearse it before your event.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What time does the band arrive?</span>
          <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-item__answer">
          <p>Sound check happens during the venue's quiet time, typically an hour before cocktail hour. Load in starts before that. Your planner gets a detailed schedule with exact arrival and setup times for the day.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Do you provide your own sound equipment?</span>
          <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-item__answer">
          <p>Yes. We bring a professional sound system sized to your venue and guest count, plus our own stage lighting rig. If your venue has in house production, we coordinate with their team in advance so everything's dialed in before doors open.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Who handles emcee duties?</span>
          <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-item__answer">
          <p>Adrian handles emcee for every event. That means introductions, toasts, special dances, and every transition between moments. We coordinate the flow directly with your planner so every moment hits its mark without the night feeling rehearsed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What happens if our event date changes?</span>
          <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-item__answer">
          <p>Date changes happen. Reach out as early as possible and we'll look at what's open. Rescheduling terms are spelled out in your contract before you sign, so you know exactly where you stand.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How do you coordinate with our wedding planner?</span>
          <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-item__answer">
          <p>Your planner is our main point of contact leading up to the event. We send them a detailed timeline, stage plot, and load in schedule. On the day of, we check in with them directly and follow their lead on transitions and timing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What genres does the band play?</span>
          <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-item__answer">
          <p>Motown, Top 40, R&B, Latin, classic rock, country, jazz standards, and more. Our music director arranges every song for live performance. We don't hand out a fixed song list and ask you to pick from it. You tell us what your crowd loves, and we build the set around that.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="faq-cta section--dark">
    <div class="faq-cta__inner">
      <h2 class="faq-cta__headline" data-reveal>Check availability for your date</h2>
      <a href="/book" class="faq-cta__button" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">Check Availability</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const items = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item');

    items.forEach(item => {
      const question = item.querySelector('.faq-item__question');
      const answer = item.querySelector('.faq-item__answer') as HTMLElement;

      question?.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const isOpen = question.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';

        // Close all other items
        items.forEach(other => {
          if (other !== item) {
            const otherQuestion = other.querySelector('.faq-item__question');
            const otherAnswer = other.querySelector('.faq-item__answer') as HTMLElement;
            otherQuestion?.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
            if (otherAnswer) {
              otherAnswer.style.maxHeight = '0';
            }
          }
        });

        // Toggle current item
        question.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(!isOpen));
        if (answer) {
          if (!isOpen) {
            answer.style.maxHeight = answer.scrollHeight + 'px';
          } else {
            answer.style.maxHeight = '0';
          }
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>

<style is:global>
  /* Hero */
  .faq-hero {
    padding: var(--section-padding) var(--content-padding) 80px;
    padding-top: calc(72px + var(--section-padding));
    text-align: center;
  }

  .faq-hero__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-optical-sizing: auto;
    font-size: var(--text-page-headline);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: var(--line-height-headline);
    color: var(--color-black);
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Shared label style */
  .faq-label {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    color: var(--color-dim);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  /* Accordion */
  .faq-accordion {
    padding: 0 var(--content-padding) var(--section-padding);
  }

  .faq-accordion__inner {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* FAQ Item */
  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  .faq-item:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  .faq-item__question {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
    padding: 24px 0;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-black);
    text-align: left;
  }

  .faq-item__question:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--color-black);
    outline-offset: 4px;
  }

  /* Toggle icon */
  .faq-item__icon {
    position: relative;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 16px;
    height: 16px;
    transition: transform 200ms ease-out;
  }

  .faq-item__icon::before,
  .faq-item__icon::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    background: var(--color-black);
    transition: transform 200ms ease-out;
  }

  .faq-item__icon::before {
    width: 16px;
    height: 1.5px;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  }

  .faq-item__icon::after {
    width: 1.5px;
    height: 16px;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  }

  /* Open state: rotate + to x */
  .faq-item__question[aria-expanded="true"] .faq-item__icon::before {
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(45deg);
  }

  .faq-item__question[aria-expanded="true"] .faq-item__icon::after {
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(45deg);
  }

  /* Answer */
  .faq-item__answer {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 200ms ease-out;
  }

  .faq-item__answer p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-black);
    padding: 0 0 24px 0;
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .faq-cta {
    padding: var(--section-padding) var(--content-padding);
  }

  .faq-cta__inner {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .faq-cta__headline {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-optical-sizing: auto;
    font-size: var(--text-section-headline);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-cream);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .faq-cta__button {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-cream);
    color: var(--color-black);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-button);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 14px 32px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0;
    transition: background-color var(--transition-default);
  }

  .faq-cta__button:hover {
    background: #ffffff;
  }

  .faq-cta__button:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--color-cream);
    outline-offset: 4px;
  }

  /* Mobile */
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .faq-hero {
      padding-top: calc(72px + 80px);
      padding-bottom: 60px;
    }

    .faq-item__question {
      font-size: 16px;
    }
  }
</style>
